race.comment: BOLD CHANGE (1) is unlucky still to be a maiden placing in four of six overall and strikes a very winnable contest here. Gets Wiggins on board from a low draw and should be going very close to shedding the maiden tag. AUTUMN GALE (4) is facing the starter for the first time but has shown a bunch of ability at the trials and won't need to be a superstar to be competitive against this lot. Respect any push in betting. SUMICH (5) strips fitter second-up from the break and gets some weight relief with the 2kg claim. Top-three credentials. ANTHROPOLOGY (6) went down by the narrowest of margins here at the latest effort and won't need to improve much to feature in the outcome.
